<h1>Raam Dev</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="https://raam.org/now">raam.org/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Nomadic
NY
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Lead Developer at WebSharks, Inc.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I hike mountains, build open-source WordPress software, and investigate the future of humanity through writing and ruminating.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Life is fascinating and compels me to explore, the transitory nature of time compels me to write, and I build open-source software to support my family and make the brain of humanity (the web) a better place to create and explore.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
We should avoid the pointless activity of defining or describing ourselves; that's not our job. Our job is to be and do the things that we wish to be defined by.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Read Leo Babauta's tribute to Scott Dinsmore who passed away climbing Mt.  Kilimanjaro: <a href="http://zenhabits.net/scott/">http://zenhabits.net/scott/</a> and then read Scott Dinsmore's last blog post before he went on his trip: <a href="http://liveyourlegend.net/disconnect-to-connect/">http://liveyourlegend.net/disconnect-to-connect/</a>
</p>

